    "Griffin Perry is a cofounder of Fermi America, an Amarillo, Texas-based data center real estate investment trust.",
    "Perry launched the firm in January 2025 with his father, former energy secretary and former Texas governor Rick Perry, and fellow billionaire Toby Neugebauer.",
    "The cofounders took Fermi public just nine months later on the Nasdaq at a $12.5 billion valuation; Perry owns an 11% stake.",
    "Fermi is planning to build an 11-gigawatt energy and data center campus on a 5,236-acre site in Amarillo, Texas.",
    "Perry also serves on the board of publicly traded oil and gas exploration and production company Granite Ridge Resources."
